1- Create folders of models, controllers, data....
2-Create a database in mysql and write the properties including the hibernate.

And what is Hibernate? That block of configuration is for JPA (Java Persistence API) and Hibernate,
which is the default ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) tool used by Spring Boot. Here's what each setting does:
This setting controls how Hibernate automatically handles your database schema (tables, columns, etc.) based
 on your Java entity classes.

